---
import LegalPage from '~/layouts/LegalPage.astro'
import { FAMILY } from '~/lib/family'
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '~/lib/siteConfig'

const updated = FAMILY.legalUpdated
---

<LegalPage
  title={`terms — ${SITE_CONFIG.name}`}
  description={`The rules for using ${SITE_CONFIG.origin}.`}
  heading="Terms of use"
  updated={updated}
  crumbLabel="terms"
>
  <p>
    By using {SITE_CONFIG.origin} or any <code>*.oriz.in</code> site, you
    agree to these terms. They are short on purpose.
  </p>

  <h2>Use the sites lawfully</h2>
  <p>
    Don&rsquo;t try to break the sites, scrape them at abusive rates, or use them
    to harass others. Account takeover, copyright infringement, and any
    activity prohibited under Indian law are forbidden.
  </p>

  <h2>Content is provided as-is</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE_CONFIG.name} is provided for information and convenience only. It
    is not professional advice. See the full
    <a href="/legal/disclaimer/">disclaimer</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Your content</h2>
  <p>
    Your journal entries stay yours. You grant {SITE_CONFIG.name} a limited
    licence to store and serve that content back to you. We do not read,
    train on, or share your entries.
  </p>

  <h2>Termination</h2>
  <p>
    You can delete your account at any time from the
    <a href="/account/">account page</a>. We can suspend accounts engaged in
    abuse without notice.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, oriz and its operator are not
    liable for any indirect or consequential damages arising from use of
    the sites.
  </p>

  <h2>Governing law</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are governed by the laws of {FAMILY.jurisdiction.country}.
    Disputes will be settled in the courts of {FAMILY.jurisdiction.city},
    {FAMILY.jurisdiction.state}.
  </p>
</LegalPage>
